On the 27 shared benchmarks, \textsc{LiquidPy} achieves
85.2\% accuracy versus PyTea's 77.8\%.  \textsc{LiquidPy}
handles 10 additional cases that PyTea fundamentally cannot:
device mismatch detection (3), phase-dependent bugs (2), and
architecture-level composition errors (5).

\paragraph{Where PyTea wins.}
PyTea's abstract interpretation handles certain reshape
patterns with non-linear dimension arithmetic more precisely
than our Z3 encoding, accounting for the shared case where
both tools fail.

\subsection{Cross-Domain Bug Detection}\label{sec:cross-domain}

We evaluate the product theory's ability to detect bugs that span
multiple domains on 27 benchmarks across 8 bug categories
(Table~\ref{tab:cross-domain}).

