\midrule
Shape-only          & 13 & 0 & 54.2\% & 0.703 \\
Device-only         & 16 & 0 & 66.7\% & 0.800 \\
Phase-only          &  0 & 0 &  0.0\% & 0.000 \\
\textbf{Full product} & \textbf{22} & \textbf{0} & \textbf{91.7\%} & \textbf{0.957} \\
\bottomrule
\end{tabular}
\end{table}

The full product theory catches 22 of 24 bugs with zero false
positives. Key findings:
\begin{itemize}[leftmargin=2em]
  \item \textbf{Shape+device bugs} (7 benchmarks): cross-device
    parameter mismatches in Linear, Conv2d, Embedding, and LSTM
    layers---undetectable by any shape-only tool.
  \item \textbf{Shape+phase bugs} (3 benchmarks): BatchNorm
    dimension interactions with train/eval mode.
  \item \textbf{Triple-domain bugs} (3 benchmarks): Transformer,
    GAN, and autoencoder models with shape+device+phase
    interactions.
  \item \textbf{vs.\ PyTea}: 19 of 24 bugs are structurally
    uncatchable by PyTea, which has no device or phase domain.
\end{itemize}

