\end{table}

The contract discovery loop achieves 100\% accuracy across all
8 benchmarks, converging in an average of 1.75 iterations.
Key predicates discovered include dimension constraints propagated
from layer parameters:
\texttt{x.shape[-1] == 768} (for \texttt{Linear(768, 10)}),
\texttt{x.shape[-1] == 512} (for \texttt{Linear(512, 256)}),
\texttt{x.shape[-1] == 1024} (for \texttt{Linear(1024, 512)}),
\texttt{x.shape[1] == 3} (for \texttt{Conv2d(3, 32, 3)}), and
\texttt{a.shape[-1] == 100} (for \texttt{Linear(100, 50)}).
The most complex case (U-Net-skip) requires 3 iterations to
discover the encoder--decoder dimension matching across skip
connections.

