\paragraph{Key findings.}
\begin{enumerate}[leftmargin=2em]
  \item \textbf{Device tracking adds 11.1 percentage points}
    (72.2\%~$\to$~83.3\%), catching device mismatch bugs
    invisible to shape-only analysis.
  \item \textbf{Phase tracking adds 5.6 points} (83.3\%~$\to$~88.9\%),
    catching a dropout-in-eval and a batchnorm-statistics bug.
  \item \textbf{Contract discovery adds 5.5 points} (88.9\%~$\to$~94.4\%),
    discovering implicit contracts that the base analysis misses.
    The contract discovery loop achieves 100\% accuracy on its
    8 dedicated benchmarks.
  \item \textbf{Quality filtering} maintains the same accuracy on the
    18-benchmark suite while providing a safety net against
    counterproductive predicate accumulation at scale.
    On the separate 18-model CEGAR ablation benchmark
    (Table~\ref{tab:cegar-ablation}), the quality-filtered pipeline
    achieves F1=0.94 with perfect recall.
  \item \textbf{Guard harvesting} for contract discovery (an
    alternative to the counterexample-guided loop that extracts
    predicates from assertions
    in \texttt{forward}) achieves 77.8\%, below the contract
    discovery loop's 94.4\%.
    The contract discovery loop discovers contracts not present
    in the source code.
\end{enumerate}

